%N A208295 a(n)*(a(n)+1) + A002973(n)^2 = A005098(n), n>=1.
%C A208295 See the Jon Perry comment on A005098. The (even) promic number a(n)*(a(n)+1) (see A002378) when subtracted from A005098(n) (the n-th value k such that 4*k+1 is prime) leaves a square, namely A002973(n)^2. E.g., n=4: 7 - 2*3 = 1^1. n=5: 9 - 0 = 3^2.
%C A208295 2*a(n)+1 = A002972(n), n>=1. E.g., n=4: 2*2+1=5.
%F A208295 a(n) = (sqrt(4*(k(n) - m(n)^2)+1)-1)/2, n>=1, with k(n) := A005098(n) (4*k(n)+1 is the prime A002144(n)) and m(n):= A002973(n).
%F A208295 a(n) = (A002972(n)-1)/2, n>=1.
